  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Mesomedes, Cithara player and lyric poet from Crete, freedman of 
    Hadrian (according to the Suda), main period of production AD 144 (according to Eusebius). Besides two poems
    in the Anthologia Palatina (14,63) and the Anthologia Planudea (16,323), 13 poems are transmitted by 
    the manuscripts, four of which are provided with musical notation...." from Robbins, Emmet (Toronto). 
